<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN351-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. maturaip paṭaimaṅka maṉṉiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div> 
    <div xml:id="PN351">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>paṭumaṇi maruṅkiṉa paṇaittāḷ yāṉaiyuṅ</l>
<l>koṭinuṭaṅku micaiya tēru māvum</l>
<l>paṭaiyamai maṟavaroṭu tuvaṉṟik kalleṉak</l>
<l>kaṭalkaṇ ṭaṉṉa kaṇṇakaṉ ṟāṉai</l>
<l>veṉṟeṟi muraciṉ vēnta reṉṟum</l>
<l>vaṇkai yeyiṉaṉ vākai yaṉṉa</l>
<l>yivaṇalan tārā tamaikuva ralla</l>
<l>reṉṉā vatuko ṟāṉē teṇṇīrp</l>
<l>poykai mēynta cevvari nārai</l>
<l>tēṅkoṇ marutiṉ pūñciṉai muṉaiyiṟ</l>
<l>kāmaru kāñcit tuñcu</l>
<l>mēmañcāl ciṟappiṉip paṇainal lūrē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Kings with drums beaten in victory,</l>
<l>an army vast in area, as if one saw the sea,</l>
<l>noisy, filled up with bold warriors suited to [their] weapons,</l>
<l>large-footed elephants with ringing bells on their sides,</l>
<l>chariots and horses with tops swaying with flags,</l>
<l>won’t ever be content without [him] giving her beauty,</l>
<l>like the Vākai of Eyiṉaṉ with a generous hand.</l>
<l>What will become of it,</l>
<l>‒ this good village of fields of an excellence worthy of protection,</l>
<l>where the red-striped stork that grazed at the pond with clear water,</l>
<l>when it dislikes the flower branches of the honey-holding myrobalan,</l>
<l> sleeps on the desirable portia tree? </l> 
</lg> 
    </div>
